verses.text: Make a joyful \w noise|strong="H7321"\w* unto \w God|strong="H0430"\w*, all ye \w lands|strong="H0776"\w*:\f + \fr 66.1 \ft all…: Heb. all the earth\f*
Sing \w forth|strong="H2167"\w* the \w honour|strong="H3519"\w* of his \w name|strong="H8034"\w*: \w make|strong="H7760"\w* his \w praise|strong="H8416"\w* \w glorious|strong="H3519"\w*.

\w Say|strong="H0559"\w* unto \w God|strong="H0430"\w*, How \w terrible|strong="H3372"\w* \add art thou in\add* thy \w works|strong="H4639"\w*! through the \w greatness|strong="H7230"\w* of thy \w power|strong="H5797"\w* shall thine \w enemies|strong="H0341"\w* \w submit|strong="H3584"\w* themselves unto thee.\f + \fr 66.3 \ft submit…: or, yield feigned obedience: Heb. lie\f*

All the \w earth|strong="H0776"\w* shall \w worship|strong="H7812"\w* thee, and shall \w sing|strong="H2167"\w* unto thee; they shall \w sing|strong="H2167"\w* \add to\add* thy \w name|strong="H8034"\w*. \w Selah|strong="H5542"\w*.

\w Come|strong="H3212"\w* and \w see|strong="H7200"\w* the \w works|strong="H4659"\w* of \w God|strong="H0430"\w*: \add he is\add* \w terrible|strong="H3372"\w* \add in his\add* \w doing|strong="H5949"\w* toward the \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w men|strong="H0120"\w*.

He \w turned|strong="H2015"\w* the \w sea|strong="H3220"\w* into \w dry|strong="H3004"\w* \add land:\add* they \w went|strong="H5674"\w* through the \w flood|strong="H5104"\w* on \w foot|strong="H7272"\w*: there did we \w rejoice|strong="H8055"\w* in him.

He \w ruleth|strong="H4910"\w* by his \w power|strong="H1369"\w* for \w ever|strong="H5769"\w*; his \w eyes|strong="H5869"\w* \w behold|strong="H6822"\w* the \w nations|strong="H1471"\w*: let not the \w rebellious|strong="H5637"\w* \w exalt|strong="H7311"\w* themselves. \w Selah|strong="H5542"\w*.
O \w bless|strong="H1288"\w* our \w God|strong="H0430"\w*, ye \w people|strong="H5971"\w*, and make the \w voice|strong="H6963"\w* of his \w praise|strong="H8416"\w* to be \w heard|strong="H8085"\w*:

Which \w holdeth|strong="H7760"\w* our \w soul|strong="H5315"\w* in \w life|strong="H2416"\w*, and \w suffereth|strong="H5414"\w* not our \w feet|strong="H7272"\w* to be \w moved|strong="H4132"\w*.\f + \fr 66.9 \ft holdeth: Heb. putteth\f*
For thou, O \w God|strong="H0430"\w*, hast \w proved|strong="H0974"\w* us: thou hast \w tried|strong="H6884"\w* us, as \w silver|strong="H3701"\w* is \w tried|strong="H6884"\w*.
Thou \w broughtest|strong="H0935"\w* us into the \w net|strong="H4686"\w*; thou \w laidst|strong="H7760"\w* \w affliction|strong="H4157"\w* upon our \w loins|strong="H4975"\w*.

Thou hast caused \w men|strong="H0582"\w* to \w ride|strong="H7392"\w* over our \w heads|strong="H7218"\w*; we \w went|strong="H0935"\w* through \w fire|strong="H0784"\w* and through \w water|strong="H4325"\w*: but thou broughtest us \w out|strong="H3318"\w* into a \w wealthy|strong="H7310"\w* \add place\add*.\f + \fr 66.12 \ft wealthy: Heb. moist\f*
I will \w go|strong="H0935"\w* into thy \w house|strong="H1004"\w* with burnt \w offerings|strong="H5930"\w*: I will \w pay|strong="H7999"\w* thee my \w vows|strong="H5088"\w*,

Which my \w lips|strong="H8193"\w* have \w uttered|strong="H6475"\w*, and my \w mouth|strong="H6310"\w* hath \w spoken|strong="H1696"\w*, when I was in \w trouble|strong="H6862"\w*.\f + \fr 66.14 \ft uttered: Heb. opened\f*

I will \w offer|strong="H5927"\w* unto thee burnt \w sacrifices|strong="H5930"\w* of \w fatlings|strong="H4220"\w*, with the \w incense|strong="H7004"\w* of \w rams|strong="H0352"\w*; I will \w offer|strong="H6213"\w* \w bullocks|strong="H1241"\w* with \w goats|strong="H6260"\w*. \w Selah|strong="H5542"\w*.\f + \fr 66.15 \ft fatlings: Heb. marrow\f*

\w Come|strong="H3212"\w* \add and\add* \w hear|strong="H8085"\w*, all ye that \w fear|strong="H3373"\w* \w God|strong="H0430"\w*, and I will \w declare|strong="H5608"\w* what he hath \w done|strong="H6213"\w* for my \w soul|strong="H5315"\w*.
I \w cried|strong="H7121"\w* unto him with my \w mouth|strong="H6310"\w*, and he was \w extolled|strong="H7311"\w* \w with|strong="H8478"\w* my \w tongue|strong="H3956"\w*.
If I \w regard|strong="H7200"\w* \w iniquity|strong="H0205"\w* in my \w heart|strong="H3820"\w*, the \w Lord|strong="H0136"\w* will not \w hear|strong="H8085"\w* \add me:\add*

\add But\add* \w verily|strong="H0403"\w* \w God|strong="H0430"\w* hath \w heard|strong="H8085"\w* \add me;\add* he hath \w attended|strong="H7181"\w* to the \w voice|strong="H6963"\w* of my \w prayer|strong="H8605"\w*.
\w Blessed|strong="H1288"\w* \add be\add* \w God|strong="H0430"\w*, which hath not turned \w away|strong="H5493"\w* my \w prayer|strong="H8605"\w*, nor his \w mercy|strong="H2617"\w* from me.
